# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MTB Platform — environment example
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (it is gitignored) and fill in your key. It powers
# every Anthropic-backed feature, each a Cloudflare Pages Function that calls the
# Messages API server-side:
#   • functions/api/litreview.ts — the appraisal agent (appraise → verify cited
#     PMIDs against PubMed → revise); the "Run robust-lit-review" button
#   • functions/api/summary.ts   — the "MTB AI summary"
#   • functions/api/narrate.ts   — the case-deck narration
#
# The key is used ONLY server-side (as a Cloudflare Pages secret). It is never
# bundled into the frontend and never committed. Without it, those buttons simply
# show a "set the key to enable" hint and fall back gracefully — nothing else
# breaks (VCF parsing, reports, notes, and the audit trail all run key-free).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- How to get an Anthropic API key ---------------------------------------
# 1. Go to the Anthropic Console:      https://console.anthropic.com/
# 2. Sign in (or create an account).
# 3. Open  Settings → API keys  ( https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys ).
# 4. Click "Create Key", name it (e.g. "mtb-platform"), copy the value.
#    It starts with  sk-ant-  and is shown ONCE — store it now.
# 5. Add billing/credits under  Settings → Billing  (a new account needs a
#    little credit; pay-as-you-go). Hackathon participants received $200 in
#    API credit + Claude Max — use that key here.
# 6. Paste it below, then push it to the deployed site:
#        pnpm secret        # reads this file, sets the Cloudflare Pages secret
#    (or run it directly:  bash scripts/push-secret.sh )
#
# Docs: https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/getting-started
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Required: your Anthropic API key (keep this file out of git — it is gitignored)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional: model for the AI summary. Defaults to a fast, low-cost model.
#   claude-haiku-4-5-20251001   fast + cheap (default)
#   claude-sonnet-5             higher quality
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001

# Optional (build only): where scripts/build-data.mjs reads the NGS pipeline
# output. Defaults to the maintainer's path; only needed to regenerate data.
# NGS_REPORTS=/path/to/ngs-tertiary-analysis-skills/reports
